      "writtenOn": "2026-07-01T01:37:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think they serve completely different purposes in terms of timing and semantics:\n\nResetRecommended is a predictive warning.\n\"An error occurred, so we recommend you perform a reset later.\n\nResetActivated is a reactive event log.\nA hardware reset signal (System/PCIe) was just detected/triggered right now.\n\nSince we are logging the actual occurrence of various reset events rather than suggesting a future recovery action, ResetRecommended is not applicable here.",
      "parentUuid": "50daa0cd_49af2d8c",
      "revId": "272014c1437960ac5c1516b1586957894df2c31a",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
